<li id="cite_note-Benabid-28">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Benabid_28-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Benabid_28-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Benabid AL, Wallace B, Mitrofanis J, Xia R, Piallat B, Chabardes S, Berger F. (2005). "A putative generalized model of the effects and mechanism of action of high frequency electrical stimulation of the central nervous system". <i>Acta Neurol Belg</i>. 2005 Sep;105(3):149–57. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16255153" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16255153">PMID 16255153</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFKrauss_JK2002">Krauss JK (2002). "Deep brain stimulation for dystonia in adults. Overview and developments". <i>Stereotactic and Functional Neurosurgery</i> <b>78</b> (3–4): 168–182. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1159%2F000068963" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1159%2F000068963" rel="nofollow">10.1159/000068963</a></span>. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12652041" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12652041">PMID 12652041</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Deep+brain+stimulation+for+dystonia+in+adults.+Overview+and+developments&amp;rft.jtitle=Stereotactic+and+Functional+Neurosurgery&amp;rft.aulast=Krauss+JK&amp;rft.au=Krauss+JK&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.volume=78&amp;rft.issue=3%E2%80%934&amp;rft.pages=168%E2%80%93182&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1159%2F000068963&amp;rft_id=info:pmid/12652041&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Deep_brain_stimulation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> Velasco F, Velasco M, Velasco AL, Jimenez F, Marquez I, Rise M (1995). "Electrical stimulation of the centromedian thalamic nucleus in control of seizures: long-term studies". <i>Epilepsia</i> 36: 63–71. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8001511" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8001511">PMID 8001511</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFBurn_D.2C_Troster_A2004">Burn D, Troster A (2004). "Neuropsychiatric Complications of Medical and Surgical Therapies for Parkinson's Disease". <i>Journal of Geriatric Psychiatry and Neurology</i> <b>17</b> (3): 172–180. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1177%2F0891988704267466" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1177%2F0891988704267466" rel="nofollow">10.1177/0891988704267466</a></span>. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15312281" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15312281">PMID 15312281</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Neuropsychiatric+Complications+of+Medical+and+Surgical+Therapies+for+Parkinson%27s+Disease&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Geriatric+Psychiatry+and+Neurology&amp;rft.aulast=Burn+D%2C+Troster+A&amp;rft.au=Burn+D%2C+Troster+A&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=17&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=172%E2%80%93180&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1177%2F0891988704267466&amp;rft_id=info:pmid/15312281&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Deep_brain_stimulation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFSmeding_H.2C_Speelman_J.2C_Koning-Haanstra_M.2C_et_al2006">Smeding H, Speelman J, Koning-Haanstra M, et al (2006). "Neuropsychological effects of bilateral STN stimulation in Parkinson disease: A controlled study". <i>Neurology</i> <b>66</b> (12): 1830–1836. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1212%2F01.wnl.0000234881.77830.66" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1212%2F01.wnl.0000234881.77830.66" rel="nofollow">10.1212/01.wnl.0000234881.77830.66</a></span>. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16801645" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16801645">PMID 16801645</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Neuropsychological+effects+of+bilateral+STN+stimulation+in+Parkinson+disease%3A+A+controlled+study&amp;rft.jtitle=Neurology&amp;rft.aulast=Smeding+H%2C+Speelman+J%2C+Koning-Haanstra+M%2C+et+al&amp;rft.au=Smeding+H%2C+Speelman+J%2C+Koning-Haanstra+M%2C+et+al&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.volume=66&amp;rft.issue=12&amp;rft.pages=1830%E2%80%931836&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1212%2F01.wnl.0000234881.77830.66&amp;rft_id=info:pmid/16801645&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Deep_brain_stimulation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
